    <div class="tsk-refs">
      <h4>&#x1f517; Cross-References (Treasury of Scripture Knowledge)</h4>
      <a href="../interlinear/hag-2.html">Hag 2 20-Zech 1 1</a> <a href="../interlinear/mat-1.html">Matt 1 12-Matt 1 13</a> <a href="../interlinear/exo-4.html">Exod 4 13</a> <a href="../interlinear/2ki-14.html">2Kgs 14 25</a> <a href="../interlinear/hag-2.html">Hag 2 10</a> <a href="../interlinear/hag-1.html">Hag 1 12</a> <a href="../interlinear/ezr-2.html">Ezra 2 63</a> <a href="../interlinear/neh-7.html">Neh 7 7</a> <a href="../interlinear/ezr-3.html">Ezra 3 8</a> <a href="../interlinear/hag-2.html">Hag 2 4</a> <a href="../interlinear/1ch-3.html">1Chr 3 19</a> <a href="../interlinear/ezr-4.html">Ezra 4 2</a> <a href="../interlinear/1ch-3.html">1Chr 3 17</a> <a href="../interlinear/1ch-6.html">1Chr 6 14-1Chr 6 15</a> <a href="../interlinear/hag-2.html">Hag 2 1-Hag 2 2</a> 
    </div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> The **second year of Darius the king** implicitly means the second year of the reign of Darius as king. You could include this information if that would be helpful to your readers, here and in 1:15 and 2:10. Alternate translation: [In the second year of the reign of King Darius]
    </div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> If your language does not use ordinal numbers, in your translation you could use cardinal numbers or equivalent expressions. Alternate translation: [In year two of … on day one of month six]
    </div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> The **sixth** month of the Hebrew calendar includes August and September on Western calendars. See the introduction to Haggai for a discussion of how you might express this date in your translation.
